    • Field Detail

      • DefaultInferenceLevel

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam DefaultInferenceLevel
        Integer control parameter. This parameter specifies the general inference level for constraints whose particular inference level is IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Default. Possible values for this parameter (in increasing order of inference strength) are IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Low, IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Basic, IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Medium, and IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Extended. The default value is IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Basic.

      • AllDiffInferenceLevel

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam AllDiffInferenceLevel
        Integer control parameter. This parameter specifies the inference level for every IloAllDiff constraint extracted to the invoking IloCPEngine instance. Possible values for this parameter are IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Default, IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Low, IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Basic, IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Medium, and IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Extended. The default value is IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Default, which allows the inference strength of all IloAllDiff constraints to be controlled via IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.DefaultInferenceLevel.

      • LogVerbosity

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam LogVerbosity
        Integer control parameter. This parameter determines the verbosity of the search log. The possible values are IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Quiet, IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Terse, IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Normal, and IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Verbose. Mode IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Quiet does not display any information, the other modes display progressively more information. The default value is IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Normal. The CP Optimizer search log is meant for visual inspection only, not for mechanized parsing. In particular, the log may change from version to version of CP Optimizer in order to improve the quality of information displayed in the log. Any code based on the log output for correct functioning may have to be updated when a new version of CP Optimizer is released.

      • LogPeriod

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam LogPeriod
        Integer control parameter. The CP Optimizer search log includes information that is displayed periodically. This parameter controls how often that information is displayed. By setting this parameter to a value of k, the log is displayed every k branches (search decisions).

      • SearchType

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam SearchType
        Integer control parameter. This parameter determines the type of search that is applied when solving a problem. When set to IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.DepthFirst, a regular depth-first search is applied. When set to IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Restart, a depth-first search that restarts from time to time is applied. When set to IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.MultiPoint, a method that combines a set of - possibly partial - solutions is applied. When set to IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Auto in sequential mode, this value chooses the appropriate search method to be used. In general IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Auto will be the Restart search. The default value is IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Auto. In parallel mode (i.e, when the number of workers is greater than one - see the IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Workers parameter), the different searches described above are spread over the workers. When the value of IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.SearchType is IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Auto, then the decision of choosing the search type for a worker is automatically made; otherwise, all workers execute the same type of search. Note that in the latter case, the workers will not do the same exploration due to some randomness introduced to break ties in decision making.

      • RandomSeed

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam RandomSeed
        Integer control parameter. The search uses some randomization in some strategies. This parameter sets the seed of the random generator used by these strategies Possible values range from 0 to IloCPEngine.IntMax. The default value is 0.

      • RestartFailLimit

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam RestartFailLimit
        Integer control parameter. When IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.SearchType is set to IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Restart, a depth-first search is restarted after a certain number of failures. This parameter controls the number of failures that must occur before restarting search. Possible values range from 0 to IloCPEngine.IntMax. The default value is 100. This value can increase after each restart: see the parameter RestartGrowthFactor.

      • MultiPointNumberOfSearchPoints

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam MultiPointNumberOfSearchPoints
        Integer control parameter. This parameter controls the number of (possibly partial) solutions manipulated by the multi-point search algorithm. The default value is 30. A larger value will diversify the search, with possible improvement in solution quality at the expense of a longer run time. A smaller value will intensify the search, resulting in faster convergence at the expense of solution quality. Note that memory consumption increases proportionally to this parameter, for each search point must store each decision variable domain.

      • PropagationLog

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam PropagationLog

      • DynamicProbing

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam DynamicProbing
        Integer control parameter. This parameter controls probing carried out during search. Probing can be useful on some problems as it can make stronger inferences on combinations of constraints. Possible values for this parameter are IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.On (dynamic probing is activated with a constant strength), IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Auto (dynamic probing is activated and its strength is adjusted adaptively) and IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Off (dynamic probing is deactivated). The strength of probing can be defined by parameter DynamicProbingStrength. Dynamic probing only has an effect when using the "Restart" (IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Restart) search type, on problems without interval variables. The default value of this parameter is IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Auto.

      • PrecedenceInferenceLevel

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam PrecedenceInferenceLevel
        Integer control parameter. This parameter specifies the inference level for precedence constraints between interval variables extracted to the invoking IloCPEngine instance. Possible values for this parameter are IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Default, IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Low, IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Basic, IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Medium, and IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Extended. The default value is IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Default, which allows the inference strength for precedence constraints between interval variables to be controlled via IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.DefaultInferenceLevel.

      • IntervalSequenceInferenceLevel

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam IntervalSequenceInferenceLevel
        Integer control parameter. This parameter specifies the inference level for the maintenance of the domain of every interval sequence variable IloIntervalSequenceVar extracted to the invoking IloCPEngine instance. Possible values for this parameter are IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Default, IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Low, IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Basic, IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Medium, and IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Extended. The default value is IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Default, which allows the inference strength of all IloIntervalSequenceVar to be controlled via IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.DefaultInferenceLevel. For more information on interval sequence variables see the concept Interval variable sequencing in CP Optimizer.

      • TimeMode

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam TimeMode
        Integer control parameter. This parameter defines how time is measured in CP Optimizer, the two legal values being IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.ElapsedTime and IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.CPUTime. CP Optimizer uses time for both display purposes and for limiting the search via IloCPEngine.NumParam.TimeLimit. Note that when multiple processors are available and the number of workers (IloCPEngine.IntParam.Workers) is greater than one, then the CPU time can be greater than the elapsed time by a factor up to the number of workers. The default value is IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.ElapsedTime.

      • TemporalRelaxation

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam TemporalRelaxation
        Integer control parameter. This advanced parameter can be used to control the usage of a temporal relaxation internal to the invoking IloCPEngine engine. This parameter can take values IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.On or IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Off, with IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.On being the default, meaning the relaxation is used in the engine when needed. For some models, using the relaxation becomes inefficient, and you may deactivate the use of the temporal relaxation using value IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Off.

      • Presolve

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam Presolve
        Integer control parameter. This parameter controls the presolve of the model to produce more compact formulations and to achieve more domain reduction. Possible values for this parameter are IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.On (presolve is activated) and IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Off (presolve is deactivated). The default value is IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.On.

      • ModelAnonymizer

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam ModelAnonymizer
        This parameter controls anonymization of a model dumped via dumpModel. The legal values of this parameter are IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Off and IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.On. The default is IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Off. When the anonymizer is off, then names of variables and constraints in the model may be found in the output file. When the anonymizer is on, names given to variables or constraints in the model will not be reflected in the output file and standard anonymized names will be used.

      • FailureDirectedSearch

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam FailureDirectedSearch
        This parameter controls usage of failure-directed search. Failure-directed search assumes that there is no (better) solution or that such a solution is very hard to find. Therefore it focuses on systematic exploration of the search space, first eliminating assignments that are most likely to fail. Failure-directed search is used only for scheduling problems (i.e. models containing interval variables) and only when the parameter IloCPEngine.IntParam.SearchType is set to IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Restart or IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Auto. Legal values for the IloCPEngine.IntParam.FailureDirectedSearch parameter are IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.On (the default) and IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Off. When the value is IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.On then CP Optimizer starts failure-directed search when other search strategies are (no longer) successful and when the memory necessary for the search does not exceed the value set by parameter IloCPEngine.IntParam.FailureDirectedSearchMaxMemory. Setting IloCPEngine.IntParam.FailureDirectedSearch to IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Off disables the feature.

      • FailureDirectedSearchMaxMemory

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam FailureDirectedSearchMaxMemory
        This parameter controls the maximum amount of memory (in bytes) available to failure-directed search. The default value is 104,857,600 (100MB). For more information about failure-directed search see IloCPEngine.IntParam.FailureDirectedSearch. Failure-directed search can sometimes consume a lot of memory, especially when end times of interval variables are not bounded. Therefore it is usually not started immediately, but only when the effective horizon (time period over which CP Optimizer must reason) becomes small enough for failure-directed search to operate inside the memory limit specified by this parameter. For many types of scheduling problems, the effective horizon tends to reduce when CP Optimizer finds a better solution (often most significantly when the initial solution is found). Therefore, when each new solution is found, CP Optimizer decides whether or not to turn on failure-directed search. Note that this parameter does not influence the effectiveness of failure-directed search, once started. Its purpose is only to control the point at which failure-directed search will begin to function.

      • UseFileLocations

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam UseFileLocations

        This parameter controls whether CP Optimizer processes file locations. With each constraint, variable or expression it is possible to associate a source file location (file name and line number). CP Optimizer can use locations later for reporting errors and conflicts. Locations are also included in exported/dumped models (#line directives).

        Source file locations can be provided to CP Optimizer in the following ways:

        • In the C++ API using macros ILOADD and ILOSETLOCATION.
        • In the CPO file format using #line directives.
        • In Java, locations are assigned automatically by functions IloCPEngine.add, IloCPEngine.intVar, IloCPEngine.intervalVar, IloCPEngine.intervalSequenceVar, and IloCPEngine.stateFunction unless this parameter is Off. The calling class must be compiled with debug information about line numbers and source files.
        • Currently there is no way to assign locations in C#.

        Legal values for this parameter are IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.On (the default) and IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Off. When the value is IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Off then CP Optimizer ignores locations in the input model and also does not export them in CPO file format (functions IloCPEngine#dumpModel and IloCPEngine#exportModel).

      • LogSearchTags

        public static final IloCPEngine.IntParam LogSearchTags
        Integer control parameter. This parameter controls the log activation. When set to IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.On, the engine will display failure tags (indices) in the engine log when solving the model. To specify the failures to explain, the member functions IloCPEngine.explainFailure(int failureTag) or IloCPEngine.explainFailure(int[] tagArray) needs to be called with the failure tags as the parameter. Several failures tags can be added. The member function IloCPEngine.clearExplanations() is used to clear the set of failure tags to be explained. To be able to see failure tags and explanations, the parameter IloCPEngine.IntParam.SearchType must be set to IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.DepthFirst and the parameter IloCPEngine.IntParam.Workers to 1. The default value of this parameter is IloCPEngine.ParameterValues.Off.
